      • callback

        public void callback(java.sql.ResultSet rs)
              throws java.sql.SQLException
        Callback method which is invoked by DataSource for each row found in the ResultSet of an elaborator query. The implementor should NOT attempt to loop through or close the ResultSet.
        Specified by:
        callback in interface RowCallback
        Parameters:
        rs - ResultSet containing current row returned by elaborator.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - thrown if there is a problem accessing the ResultSet.

      • getCallBackColumns

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getCallBackColumns()
        A list of column names that are used in the callback In lower case. All other column names will be processed normally. For use if you want to use callback to process some columns, but still want other columns to be set (with setBLAH)
        Specified by:
        getCallBackColumns in interface RowCallback
        Returns:
        the list of columns to skip (that are used by callback)
